Year = {2024},
Volume = {135},
Month = {SEP},
Abstract = {Advanced collaborative technologies for Artificial Intelligence of
   Things (AIoT) play main role in the development of smart technologies.
   In this article we present research results on the development of novel
   complex type -2 fuzzy control system to help in real-time measuring and
   diagnostic of vibration, temperature and air quality for optimal car
   driving. Real-time information allows the driver to be informed about
   the possibility of a potential failure. It gives a chance to avoid
   failure and related consequences. The paper presents both theoretical
   aspects of applied type -2 fuzzy control and practical constructions for
   sensors, electronics and software implementations to compose a novel
   control module implemented for car radio systems. The developed system
   was tested in various driving conditions and results of measurements and
   predictions were confirmed by the certified car diagnostic station.},
